WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:09.280
[Unknown]: Welcome to the scene in the unseen.

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:12.880
[Guest]: My guest today is Shashi Tharoor and we are going to be talking about his new book, The

00:01:12.880 --> 00:01:17.920
[Guest]: Paradoxical Prime Minister, which focuses on the many contradictions of Narendra Modi.

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:23.200
[Guest]: Now, Tharoor is an MP of the Congress Party, so you would expect him to write an anti-Modi

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:24.200
[Guest]: book.

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:27.440
[Guest]: But this book isn't simplistic and one-sided at all.

00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:30.080
[Guest]: And the facts and arguments in them speak for themselves.

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:33.560
[Guest]: He was very kind to give me an hour of his time on a very busy day for him.

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:38.240
[Guest]: We recorded late at night over Skype and I overshot the time and couldn't ask him all

00:01:38.240 --> 00:01:39.580
[Guest]: the questions I wanted to.

00:01:39.580 --> 00:01:43.200
[Guest]: But he was very forthright in all his answers to what I did ask.

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:48.720
[Guest]: We don't talk about only Modi in this chat, by the way, but also address multiple questions

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:53.600
[Guest]: about the nature of our politics, the idea of India and the paradoxes within the Congress

00:01:53.600 --> 00:01:55.120
[Guest]: Party itself.

00:01:55.120 --> 00:02:00.160
[Guest]: But before we go to that conversation, let's take a quick commercial break.

